President Muhammadu Buhari has urged Nigerians to vote for the candidate of their choice in the forthcoming general elections. Buhari told the citizens to vote without fear. Addressing Nigerians in a nationwide broadcast, Buhari vowed to ensure security of electorates during the polls. He also urged Nigerians to eschew violence and acts that could disrupt the electoral process. According to Buhari: “I urge every citizen therefore, to go out to vote for their candidates of choice without fear, because security shall be provided and your vote shall count. “I however admonish you to eschew violence and avoid actions capable of disrupting the electoral processes. I wish us all a successful General Election.”